@node "Program Description" "Program Description"
@{b}PROGRAM DESCRIPTION@{ub}

MUIWBPattern allows your Amiga to have different backdrops appear every
time you boot up.  The program can be run in two different modes:

1.  Displays an interface to allow you to create lists of images you want
    for backdrops for the Workbench, windows, and screen.

2.  Quietly choose the backdrops to be used next time you boot.


@{b}SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS@{ub}

Requires Kickstart 2.0 or higher.
Requires Magic User Interface (@{" MUI " link "MUI" 0}) Version 3.2 or higher.

Any Amiga from A500 to A4000.


@{b}FEATURES@{ub}

·  Allows random or ordered backdrop changes every time you boot.

·  Pictures can be anywhere on your system that is accessible when
   the Workbench is started.

·  If you have OS 3.0 or higher, any pictures you have dataypes for
   will work.  (GIF, JPEG...)

·  Small, under 30K.  Just one executable and two icons, no other files are
   created or installed.

·  Uses MUI.

·  Preferences are saved as icon tooltypes.

·  No system patches.

·  Uses locale library (French catalog included)


@{b}THIS ARCHIVE INCLUDES:@{ub}

